Updated [`content/papers/prior.information.md`](/home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive/content/papers/prior.information.md) with minimal QA-only structural edits.

Summary of changes:
- Added missing blank-line paragraph boundaries in places where prose and display math were visually merged.
- Normalized display-equation spacing for Hugo+KaTeX readability (blank lines before/after many `$$\tag{...}` blocks).
- Split one clearly merged sentence transition into two paragraphs near the conclusion (`... \lambda_{m+1} = 0.` then new paragraph).

Self-check:
- Paragraph boundaries now use blank lines where intended.
- In-text equation references (`Eq. (14)`, `Eq. (17)`, and range refs like `(13)-(17)`, `(26)-(28)`) resolve to tagged display equations in the document.
- No paper meaning/content or equation expressions were changed.
